HEADWORD: Terebrantia
<hw>Ter`e*bran"ti*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of Hymenoptera
including those which have an ovipositor adapted for perforating plants.
It includes the sawflies.</def>⟦br⟧
